divs: Sighting DetailsThe craft in the photos attached were taken at the cnr of Hollows beach and Captain Cook Hwy, just outside of cairns. I was taking pictures of an a amazing sunset, and took a series of shots. When I viewed these on the computer, I then became aware of the craft in the photos. I did also have 3 other shots showing the craft stationary over glacier rock, though at present I am having trouble locating them.Using an editing technique which washes out colour and any solid background, and leaves only metallic objects,,,,I was able to scan all the shots and find craft in most from that series taken on the evening in question. I will include shots using this process and the originals so as the actual shape at time of capture can be seen clearly.
Summary: I was taking photos of a very spectacular sunset. I took a series of shots. In each of the shots,,,I have craft or very unusual anomalies. I have had 4 sightings in this area,,,over a period of 35 years, the first at 13 years of age.
